IIuic errori dicto loco Christus occurrit. Christianos veteres Tertullianus jurasse ait per salutem principis omnibus geniis augustiorem. Apud Vegetium formula est, cujus et supra meminimus, qua Christiani milites jurant non per Deum tantum, sed et per majestatem Imperatoris, quae secundum Deum humano generi diligenda est et colenda.

XII. Tertullian says that the ancient Christians swore by the Safety of the Prinee. In Vegetius, as above stated, the formula is, By God and the Majesty of the Emperor, which, after God, is to be reverenced and honoured by men.

XII.
